#### events.log — Greenfield event types

Format: one JSON object per line. Always **append** — never overwrite.

| Event Type | Required Fields | When |
|-----------|----------------|------|
| `project_init` | `{ "detail": "project scaffolding started" }` | Project scaffolding begins |
| `plan_created` | `{ "source": "planner" }` | PLAN.md written |
| `architecture_created` | `{ "source": "architect" }` | ARCHITECTURE.md written |
| `blueprint_created` | `{ "source": "code-architect" }` | BLUEPRINT.md written |
| `phase_started` | `{ "phase": "<name>" }` | Any phase begins |
| `file_created` | `{ "file": "path/to/file.ts" }` | New source file created |
| `file_modified` | `{ "file": "path/to/file.ts" }` | Existing file modified |
| `test_added` | `{ "file": "path/to/test.ts" }` | Test file created |
| `test_passed` | `{ "count": N, "detail": "..." }` | All tests passing |
| `test_failed` | `{ "count": N, "detail": "..." }` | Tests failing |
| `lint_passed` | `{}` | Lint clean |
| `lint_failed` | `{ "count": N }` | Lint errors |
| `typecheck_passed` | `{}` | TypeScript type check clean |
| `phase_completed` | `{ "phase": "<name>" }` | Phase finishes |
| `review_passed` | `{}` | Code review approved |
| `review_failed` | `{ "issues": N }` | Code review flagged issues |
| `security_review_passed` | `{}` | Security review approved |
| `project_complete` | `{}` | All phases done → triggers folder rename |
| `step_rejected` | `{ "step": N, "reason": "..." }` | Step rejected by goal lock |
| `step_skipped` | `{ "step": N, "reason": "..." }` | Step skipped (unnecessary) |
| `step_rewritten` | `{ "step": N, "original": "..", "rewritten": ".." }` | Step auto-rewritten |
| `rewrite_rejected` | `{ "step": N, "reason": "..." }` | Rewrite rejected by gate |
| `drift_warning` | `{ "step": N, "reason": "...", "drift_warnings": N }` | Step flagged as drift |
| `scope_expanded` | `{ "file": "...", "reason": "..." }` | New file beyond original scope |
| `scoring_complete` | `{ "scores": {...}, "priority": [...], "rewritten": [...], "dropped": [...] }` | All steps scored |
| `blocked` | `{ "reason": "..." }` | Execution blocked |
| `state_invalid` | `{ "reason": "..." }` | states.json is malformed |
| `state_infeasible` | `{ "reason": "..." }` | No step advances a criterion |
| `state_drift_detected` | `{}` | states.json diverged from in-memory state |
| `mental_model_drift` | `{}` | In-memory state diverged from written state |

**Note:** Event `phase_started` is written ONLY by doc-updater during greenfield phase transitions. tdd-guide does NOT write this event. Events `test_added`, `lint_passed`, `lint_failed`, and `typecheck_passed` are written by tdd-guide during Phase 4 execution. `lint_passed` is written ONLY by tdd-guide during Phase 4 execution. Doc-updater does NOT write this event.

Log format example:
```
{"type":"project_init","timestamp":"2026-06-13T10:00:00Z","detail":"project scaffolding started"}
{"type":"plan_created","timestamp":"2026-06-13T10:02:00Z","source":"planner"}
{"type":"phase_completed","timestamp":"2026-06-13T10:02:00Z","phase":"plan"}
```

**Note:** All events use `"type"` (not `"event"`) for the event type field. Every event in events.log MUST include a `"timestamp"` field in ISO 8601 format.

